4. Counting Character Input
Objective: Create a form with a textarea input. Display a character counter below the textarea that updates in real-time as the user types. 
The counter should show the number of characters entered out of a maximum limit (e.g., "50/200 characters").

Steps:
Create a form with a textarea input.
Add a <div> or <span> below the textarea to display the character count.
Attach an input event listener to the textarea.
In the event handler, update the character count as the user types.